In [85]:
# numbering rows
data_h['number'] = data_h.reset_index().index

# parabolic numbers
data_h['number_2'] = data_h['number'] * data_h['number']

# hour, day of week numbers
data_h['hour'] = data_h.index.hour
data_h['dayofweek'] = data_h.index.dayofweek

# lags 12, 24, 7*24 hours
data_h['lag_12'] = data_h['num_orders'].shift(12)
data_h['lag_24'] = data_h['num_orders'].shift(24)
data_h['lag_7_24'] = data_h['num_orders'].shift(7 * 24)

# moving averages 12, 24, 7*24 hours
data_h['ma_12'] = data_h['num_orders'].shift(1).rolling(12).mean()
data_h['ma_24'] = data_h['num_orders'].shift(1).rolling(24).mean()
data_h['ma_7_24'] = data_h['num_orders'].shift(1).rolling(7 * 24).mean()

# dropping nans
data_featured = data_h.dropna()
data_featured

In [87]:
def X_y_splitting(train, test):
    X_train = train.drop(columns=['num_orders'])
    y_train = train['num_orders']
    X_test = test.drop(columns=['num_orders'])
    y_test = test['num_orders']
    return (X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test)
    
# features and targets
X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test = X_y_splitting(train, test)

print('X_train.shape =', X_train.shape)
print('y_train.shape =', y_train.shape)

print('X_test.shape =', X_test.shape)
print('y_test.shape =', y_test.shape)

X_train.shape = (3823, 10)
y_train.shape = (3823,)
X_test.shape = (425, 10)

def rmse(y_pred, y):
    return -np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_pred, y))

my_scorer = make_scorer(rmse)
